00:00:37.530 --> 00:00:40.100
of the international organizations

00:00:40.110 --> 00:00:44.060
that regulates foreign economic

00:00:44.070 --> 00:00:48.500
relations within the framework

00:00:48.510 --> 00:00:52.520
of the activities of about 150 countries.

00:00:53.040 --> 00:00:55.000
The World Trade Organization

00:00:55.010 --> 00:00:57.740
(WTO) is the first organization

00:00:57.750 --> 00:01:00.520
that regulates trade relations.

00:01:00.760 --> 00:01:03.000
The history of the establishment

00:01:03.010 --> 00:01:04.960
of the World Trade Organization.

00:01:05.760 --> 00:01:09.240
In 1947, in the postwar period, as we

00:01:09.250 --> 00:01:13.220
already know, the countries of Europe

00:01:13.230 --> 00:01:17.140
were moving to remove barriers.

00:01:17.220 --> 00:01:19.980
Since the barrier was so high

00:01:19.990 --> 00:01:22.760
in the postwar period, it

00:01:22.770 --> 00:01:25.540
was prohibitive.

00:01:27.300 --> 00:01:32.240
The US assistance under the Marshal

00:01:32.250 --> 00:01:35.140
Plan envisaged the fulfillment by all

00:01:35.150 --> 00:01:37.160
countries of the future European Union

00:01:37.170 --> 00:01:40.300
of the conditions of liberalization

00:01:40.310 --> 00:01:42.060
of foreign trade relations.

00:01:42.820 --> 00:01:45.520
Therefore, negotiations within

00:01:45.530 --> 00:01:49.260
the ministries of countries that would

00:01:49.270 --> 00:01:50.680
like to liberalize their

00:01:51.920 --> 00:01:53.600
international relations began almost

00:01:53.610 --> 00:01:58.120
immediately in the post-war period.

00:01:58.520 --> 00:02:01.760
The negotiations were long enough.

00:02:01.980 --> 00:02:05.240
As you can see, there were

00:02:05.250 --> 00:02:06.920
a lot of rounds.

00:02:07.160 --> 00:02:09.900
Each round lasted for more

00:02:10.680 --> 00:02:12.720
than a year, but a general

00:02:12.730 --> 00:02:15.540
trade tariff agreement

00:02:15.550 --> 00:02:17.840
was eventually signed.

00:02:18.860 --> 00:02:20.980
The agreements that were reached

00:02:20.990 --> 00:02:23.220
and signed within the framework of the

00:02:23.230 --> 00:02:26.180
GATT then formed the basis for

00:02:26.190 --> 00:02:28.620
the next stage of development

00:02:28.630 --> 00:02:29.880
of international regulation of

00:02:29.890 --> 00:02:32.680
foreign trade, namely the creation

00:02:32.690 --> 00:02:35.680
of the World Trade Organization.

00:02:36.140 --> 00:02:40.680
On January 1, 1995, the GATT

00:02:40.690 --> 00:02:42.620
was transformed into the World

00:02:42.630 --> 00:02:45.920
Trade Organization.

00:02:46.560 --> 00:02:49.000
In this case, as far as the

00:02:49.010 --> 00:02:51.600
Uruguayan documents signed in

00:02:51.620 --> 00:02:53.520
the Uruguayan Round, as you can

00:02:53.530 --> 00:02:56.700
see on the slide, which took

00:02:56.920 --> 00:02:59.620
place from 1986 until 1994,

00:02:59.630 --> 00:03:04.280
they formed the basis of the

00:03:04.290 --> 00:03:06.040
World Trade Organization.

00:03:06.620 --> 00:03:09.980
At present, the WTO membership is

00:03:09.990 --> 00:03:13.200
already 150 countries, which shows

00:03:13.210 --> 00:03:15.760
the interest of all the countries in

00:03:15.770 --> 00:03:18.060
the world, which maintain active

00:03:18.070 --> 00:03:20.140
foreign trade relations, to be included

00:03:20.280 --> 00:03:22.400
in the negotiation processes

00:03:22.410 --> 00:03:25.080
and interest in participation

00:03:25.090 --> 00:03:27.320
in the World Trade Organization.

00:03:27.700 --> 00:03:31.880
