Russian market.

01:03:41.280 --> 01:03:44.730
This is reflected in the fact that

01:03:44.740 --> 01:03:47.490
on the territory of the Russian

01:03:47.500 --> 01:03:51.710
regions are held regular meetings

01:03:51.720 --> 01:03:56.030
at the level of heads of regions and

01:03:56.040 --> 01:03:58.190
various communities of Russian

01:03:58.200 --> 01:04:05.170
industrialists of regional location.

01:04:05.180 --> 01:04:08.030
So, these meetings, these consultations,

01:04:08.040 --> 01:04:10.670
they allow Russian producers

01:04:10.680 --> 01:04:12.150
to find out what

01:04:12.160 --> 01:04:15.010
risks the WTO membership brings

01:04:15.020 --> 01:04:16.990
to them, and on the other

01:04:17.000 --> 01:04:18.790
hand, what advantages.

01:04:19.130 --> 01:04:21.990
And as reports on such meetings

01:04:22.000 --> 01:04:24.910
show, it turns out, often

01:04:25.270 --> 01:04:26.510
Russian industrialists

01:04:26.520 --> 01:04:28.470
and manufacturers have limited

01:04:28.480 --> 01:04:30.510
information about the advantages

01:04:30.520 --> 01:04:32.930
that the WTO gives and their

01:04:32.950 --> 01:04:35.330
idea of how and in

01:04:35.340 --> 01:04:39.530
what ways, what steps Russia

01:04:39.540 --> 01:04:42.130
will enter the WTO, about what

01:04:42.140 --> 01:04:45.330
barriers will remain

01:04:45.340 --> 01:04:47.310
for the transitional period,

01:04:47.320 --> 01:04:49.970
are quite limited.

01:04:50.050 --> 01:04:51.690
Based on this, such consultations

01:04:51.700 --> 01:04:53.510
with Russian industrial manufacturers

01:04:53.520 --> 01:04:55.110
occurring throughout the territory

01:04:55.190 --> 01:04:57.750
of Russia, they promote the

01:04:57.760 --> 01:05:00.730
understanding of this process

01:05:00.740 --> 01:05:03.530
and produce a positive response

01:05:03.540 --> 01:05:05.370
and feedback.

01:05:05.430 --> 01:05:07.210
That is, on the one hand, to accept

01:05:07.220 --> 01:05:08.970
this situation as more

01:05:08.980 --> 01:05:10.710
promising for the development of

01:05:11.030 --> 01:05:13.410
Russia, and on the other hand,

01:05:13.420 --> 01:05:15.090
to think about how to

01:05:15.100 --> 01:05:16.510
increase the competitiveness

01:05:16.520 --> 01:05:17.950
of its own production.

01:05:19.450 --> 01:05:21.270
As analytical studies show,

01:05:21.280 --> 01:05:23.690
less than 50% of Russian

01:05:23.700 --> 01:05:26.910
manufacturers thought

01:05:26.920 --> 01:05:29.750
about Russia's entry into

01:05:29.760 --> 01:05:33.590
the WTO five years ago.

01:05:33.970 --> 01:05:36.630
At present, this figure has increased

01:05:36.640 --> 01:05:40.570
sharply, and everyone understands,

01:05:40.580 --> 01:05:42.390
on the one hand, what advantages,

01:05:42.400 --> 01:05:45.110
and on the other hand, what shortcomings

01:05:45.120 --> 01:05:47.070
are related to their organizational

01:05:47.080 --> 01:05:48.970
activities and how prepared

01:05:48.980 --> 01:05:51.130
or not prepared for Russia's accession

01:05:51.140 --> 01:05:54.050
to the WTO.

01:05:54.690 --> 01:05:57.670
The next factor and task that will

01:05:57.680 --> 01:06:00.450
be solved in the framework of Russia'

01:06:00.460 --> 01:06:03.510
s accession to the WTO is Russia'

01:06:03.520 --> 01:06:07.010
s participation in the development of

01:06:07.020 --> 01:06:09.350
international trade rules

01:06:09.360 --> 01:06:11.110
and in compliance with the defense of

01:06:11.120 --> 01:06:13.410
its national interests.

01:06:13.420 --> 01:06:16.350
I have already mentioned that the Doha

01:06:16.360 --> 01:06:19.410
Round is dedicated to developing

01:06:19.420 --> 01:06:22.170
the problems of liberalization of agriculture.

01:06:22.810 --> 01:06:26.790
In this case, Russia, rich in land

01:06:26.800 --> 01:06:28.190
and natural agricultural

01:06:28.200 --> 01:06:29.930
resources and opportunities, has a

01:06:29.940 --> 01:06:33.250
high potential for the development

01:06:33.260 --> 01:06:36.430
of its agricultural sector and its

01:06:36.440 --> 01:06:41.290
development not only in the

01:06:41.300 --> 01:06:43.150
direction of ensuring domestic

01:06:43.160 --> 01:06:45.730
consumption, but also penetration

01:06:45.740 --> 01:06:48.450
into the European market.

01:06:48.550 --> 01:06:52.250
As the latest history of Russia shows,

01:06:52.260 --> 01:06:56.030
our agricultural workers do not

01:06:56.040 --> 01:06:59.610
constantly experience the situation of crisis.

01:07:00.790 --> 01:07:03.350
Each time period is repeated

01:07:03.360 --> 01:07:05.970
a fairly high harvest.

01:07:06.070 --> 01:07:08.990
But, as practice shows, often

01:07:09.130 --> 01:07:11.530
public procurement

01:07:11.540 --> 01:07:13.670
of agricultural products does

01:07:13.680 --> 01:07:16.110
not cover the excess supply of

01:07:16.120 --> 01:07:17.510
grain and other

01:07:17.520 --> 01:07:19.370
agricultural goods.

01:07:19.430 --> 01:07:21.390
And then for the next

01:07:21.400 --> 01:07:22.910
year, farmers simply reduce

01:07:22.920 --> 01:07:25.190
the volume of their production

01:07:25.200 --> 01:07:26.910
supply.

01:07:27.650 --> 01:07:29.410
As I said in my course on international

01:07:29.420 --> 01:07:30.550
economic relations, such

01:07:30.560 --> 01:07:32.630
a surplus situation in the

01:07:32.640 --> 01:07:34.950
world free space is usually

01:07:34.960 --> 01:07:37.530
solved by the fact that such

01:07:37.540 --> 01:07:40.270
naturally created surpluses

01:07:40.280 --> 01:07:42.990
and the hard work of Russian

01:07:43.000 --> 01:07:44.350
agricultural workers can

01:07:44.360 --> 01:07:46.550
be realized precisely

01:07:46.560 --> 01:07:47.950
by export.

01:07:47.960 --> 01:07:50.190
Russia, in fact, within these all

01:07:50.200 --> 01:07:52.310
sorts of quota restrictions such

01:07:52.320 --> 01:07:54.770
chances do not have or have

01:07:54.780 --> 01:07:56.710
very limited scale.

01:07:56.790 --> 01:07:59.010
In the end, this leads to negative

01:07:59.020 --> 01:08:01.090
consequences, in essence, to

01:08:01.100 --> 01:08:02.550
overproduction in some periods,

01:08:02.560 --> 01:08:04.930
in some years in agriculture

01:08:04.940 --> 01:08:06.790
and to the ruin of these

01:08:06.800 --> 01:08:08.810
agricultural ones.

01:08:09.450 --> 01:08:13.250
The next component of, say, the

01:08:13.550 --> 01:08:17.690
benefits for Russia from joining

01:08:17.700 --> 01:08:20.110
the World Trade Organization

01:08:20.120 --> 01:08:21.810
is the improvement of Russia'

01:08:21.820 --> 01:08:24.610
s image as a full participant

01:08:24.620 --> 01:08:26.810
in international

01:08:26.820 --> 01:08:28.350
trade.

01:08:28.370 --> 01:08:31.850
While Russia is not a WTO

01:08:31.860 --> 01:08:33.690
member, some countries, some

01:08:33.700 --> 01:08:34.970
governments, or some economic

01:08:34.980 --> 01:08:36.490
agents from some countries have

01:08:36.500 --> 01:08:43.490
the opportunity to discriminate

01:08:43.500 --> 01:08:45.230
against Russia and, accordingly,

01:08:45.240 --> 01:08:47.750
to prove some of their

01:08:48.410 --> 01:08:51.790
rights to discriminate

01:08:51.800 --> 01:08:54.670
against trade flows.

01:08:54.830 --> 01:08:57.890
In this case, the most case-proof

01:08:57.900 --> 01:09:00.950
example of Russia's accession

01:09:00.960 --> 01:09:04.550
to the WTO is the amendment of the

01:09:04.560 --> 01:09:09.430
INC in the United States, according

01:09:09.440 --> 01:09:13.390
to which once on the yet socialist Russia

01:09:13.400 --> 01:09:16.630
were imposed restrictions on export

01:09:16.640 --> 01:09:21.050
of advanced technologies, on discrimination,

01:09:21.060 --> 01:09:22.910
on export-import relations

01:09:22.920 --> 01:09:25.210
in connection with the restrictions

01:09:25.220 --> 01:09:26.890
that Russia then imposed

01:09:26.900 --> 01:09:30.930
on the exit of Jews from Russia.

01:09:33.390 --> 01:09:35.170
In this case, despite the fact that

01:09:35.180 --> 01:09:38.190
Russia recognizes a market economy

01:09:38.200 --> 01:09:40.630
in a new thousand words, not

01:09:40.640 --> 01:09:42.090
a transitional transformational

01:09:42.100 --> 01:09:45.070
economy, the amendment still works.

01:09:45.430 --> 01:09:47.550
And the amendment of Jones Venik

01:09:47.560 --> 01:09:52.370
is a precedent to the discriminatory

01:09:52.380 --> 01:09:54.310
attitude of Russia, although each

01:09:54.320 --> 01:09:57.350
year by the order of the president

01:09:57.360 --> 01:10:00.050
of the United States this amendment

01:10:00.060 --> 01:10:02.530
is suspended, but it is nevertheless

01:10:02.540 --> 01:10:04.150
not eliminated.

01:10:04.310 --> 01:10:05.690
Despite the fact that, suppose, the negotiations

01:10:05.790 --> 01:10:08.490
of Russia and the United States on Russia's accession

01:10:08.500 --> 01:10:10.450
to the WTO have already been completed,

01:10:10.460 --> 01:10:13.130
and the precedent of the amendment remains.

01:10:13.470 --> 01:10:15.950
And the US says that only when Russia becomes

01:10:15.960 --> 01:10:18.050
a WTO member, we will then eliminate

01:10:18.060 --> 01:10:19.470
this amendment.

01:10:19.710 --> 01:10:21.430
In this case, there is no longer

01:10:21.440 --> 01:10:23.290
the country against which the amendment

01:10:23.300 --> 01:10:25.890
was introduced, the object of this amendment

01:10:25.900 --> 01:10:28.030
has changed.

01:10:28.040 --> 01:10:29.790
Nevertheless, this political

01:10:29.800 --> 01:10:31.670
pressure persists, and in this

01:10:31.850 --> 01:10:34.650
case, the image of confrontation

01:10:34.660 --> 01:10:37.790
for Russia, when it enters

01:10:37.800 --> 01:10:40.790
some international economic

01:10:40.800 --> 01:10:43.170
relations, remains.

01:10:45.330 --> 01:10:47.870
What are the main objectives of the negotiations

01:10:47.880 --> 01:10:50.110
on Russia's accession to the WTO?

01:10:51.090 --> 01:10:53.330
First of all, as I said, we need to

01:10:53.990 --> 01:10:56.370
weigh the price of accession, that

01:10:56.380 --> 01:10:59.150
is, what benefits and advantages

01:10:59.160 --> 01:11:00.810
Russia will get from joining the

01:11:00.820 --> 01:11:03.310
WTO, to these benefits and advantages.

01:11:03.590 --> 01:11:05.010
What concessions is Russia

01:11:05.020 --> 01:11:08.010
prepared to make for this

01:11:08.020 --> 01:11:08.930
accession?

01:11:09.210 --> 01:11:10.990
To what level should it lower

01:11:11.000 --> 01:11:13.210
tariffs and to what extent, so to

01:11:13.220 --> 01:11:15.270
speak, has it opened the

01:11:15.280 --> 01:11:16.290
domestic markets?

01:11:17.130 --> 01:11:18.950
We remember that the World Trade

01:11:18.960 --> 01:11:21.410
Organization does not mean such

01:11:21.420 --> 01:11:23.070
a consistent liberalization

01:11:23.080 --> 01:11:24.550
of international economic relations

01:11:24.560 --> 01:11:27.230
and foreign trade.

01:11:27.270 --> 01:11:29.490
Despite the fact that all countries

01:11:29.500 --> 01:11:31.630
have adopted agreements on GAD, GAC,

01:11:31.790 --> 01:11:35.850
TRIPS, TRIMS, however, each country in

01:11:35.860 --> 01:11:37.130
a certain period of time introduces

01:11:37.140 --> 01:11:38.830
those restrictions that they consider

01:11:38.870 --> 01:11:40.790
reasonable, justified, and within

01:11:40.910 --> 01:11:42.250
the framework of coordination

01:11:42.260 --> 01:11:46.530
with the WTO these restrictions pass.

01:11:47.270 --> 01:11:51.770
In this case, the task of Russian representatives

01:11:51.780 --> 01:11:53.830
in the negotiations is to great

01:11:53.840 --> 01:11:57.010
advantages or at least to balance

01:11:57.020 --> 01:11:59.010
the situation of losses and benefits

01:11:59.020 --> 01:12:01.210
of Russia's withdrawal

01:12:01.220 --> 01:12:04.930
from the WTO.

01:12:07.360 --> 01:12:10.880
Regarding the GATT Goods Agreement,

01:12:13.850 --> 01:12:16.800
I would like to draw your attention

01:12:16.810 --> 01:12:19.060
to the fact that the General

01:12:19.070 --> 01:12:23.540
Agreement of 1947, as I have said,

01:12:23.550 --> 01:12:26.680
was the basis for the agreement

01:12:26.690 --> 01:12:32.660
of countries' accession to the

01:12:32.670 --> 01:12:34.380
World Trade Organization.

01:12:34.940 --> 01:12:37.400
But before the World Trade

01:12:37.410 --> 01:12:39.200
Organization was established there

01:12:39.210 --> 01:12:41.700
was a new round of negotiations,

01:12:41.710 --> 01:12:45.580
and the 1994 General Agreement

01:12:45.590 --> 01:12:51.120
contains additional positions.

01:12:51.460 --> 01:12:56.160
First, the 1994 agreement

01:12:57.440 --> 01:13:00.140
contains specific sector

01:13:00.150 --> 01:13:02.040
agreements, namely agriculture

01:13:02.050 --> 01:13:04.080
and textiles.

01:13:04.600 --> 01:13:08.340
In this regard, Russia, joining the

01:13:08.350 --> 01:13:11.280
WTO at the present stage, rather than

01:13:11.290 --> 01:13:15.000
before 1995, receives some

01:13:15.010 --> 01:13:19.300
advantages in this area, in the

01:13:19.310 --> 01:13:24.080
development of an agreement

01:13:24.090 --> 01:13:26.980
on agriculture and textile.

01:13:26.990 --> 01:13:30.460
The next component of the 1994

01:13:30.470 --> 01:13:32.600
GAD is state trade.

01:13:33.120 --> 01:13:36.240
There are negative points for Russia

01:13:36.250 --> 01:13:39.220
here, because within these agreements,

01:13:39.230 --> 01:13:43.460
government orders on foreign

01:13:43.470 --> 01:13:44.960
trade must be distributed

01:13:44.970 --> 01:13:47.580
on a market basis.

01:13:47.860 --> 01:13:51.040
The tradition of the Russian

01:13:51.050 --> 01:13:53.120
economy is associated

01:13:53.130 --> 01:13:55.740
with a certain vulgarism of officials

01:13:55.750 --> 01:13:57.080
who distribute certain

01:13:57.090 --> 01:14:01.960
state supplies and orders.

01:14:01.970 --> 01:14:04.840
The next issue is related to the

01:14:04.850 --> 01:14:07.660
standards for different products.

01:14:07.670 --> 01:14:10.180
The Russian standards have traditionally

01:14:10.190 --> 01:14:13.080
been quite high.

01:14:13.760 --> 01:14:15.660
Conditionally speaking, such a primitive

01:14:15.670 --> 01:14:17.500
example, as the amount of meat

01:14:17.510 --> 01:14:19.380
in the high quality Russian sausage,

01:14:19.390 --> 01:14:22.600
it is usually higher than the same

01:14:22.610 --> 01:14:24.540
standards, for example, concerning

01:14:24.550 --> 01:14:26.480
the European Union.

01:14:27.720 --> 01:14:30.440
But the same standards, quite

01:14:30.450 --> 01:14:33.900
strict, are introduced

01:14:33.910 --> 01:14:35.360
on medicines.

01:14:36.160 --> 01:14:39.040
And it is not by chance that, for

01:14:39.050 --> 01:14:41.060
example, India recently entered into the discussion

01:14:41.070 --> 01:14:43.740
of agreements on Russia's accession

01:14:43.750 --> 01:14:46.480
to the WTO under the GAD section.

01:14:46.680 --> 01:14:48.960
India is the largest

01:14:48.970 --> 01:14:50.700
exporter of

01:14:50.710 --> 01:14:51.840
medicines.

01:14:52.440 --> 01:14:57.320
And if Russia stands in the position

01:14:57.330 --> 01:14:59.500
of adopting such international

01:14:59.510 --> 01:15:01.400
standards, which are usually accepted

01:15:01.410 --> 01:15:03.280
in the World Trade Organization, and

01:15:03.620 --> 01:15:05.820
lower some of its standards, it

01:15:05.830 --> 01:15:07.960
is likely that this country will

01:15:07.970 --> 01:15:10.920
have a greater opportunity to

01:15:10.930 --> 01:15:13.440
penetrate the Russian market.

01:15:13.840 --> 01:15:15.840
As for subsidies.

01:15:16.880 --> 01:15:19.560
Indeed, the 1994 agreement

01:15:19.570 --> 01:15:23.340
also includes subsidy

01:15:24.280 --> 01:15:26.940
issues.

01:15:27.100 --> 01:15:28.280
Subsidies are the most painful

01:15:28.290 --> 01:15:31.500
issue in the General Agreement

01:15:31.510 --> 01:15:34.160
on Tariffs and Trade and in the

01:15:34.170 --> 01:15:36.520
current negotiations of the

01:15:36.530 --> 01:15:38.320
Doha round.

01:15:38.500 --> 01:15:38.840
Why is?

01:15:38.960 --> 01:15:39.980
First of all, it is

01:15:40.280 --> 01:15:41.500
about agricultural

01:15:41.510 --> 01:15:43.620
export subsidies.

01:15:44.040 --> 01:15:46.080
And, of course, Russia, becoming

01:15:46.090 --> 01:15:48.620
a participant in these negotiations,

01:15:48.630 --> 01:15:50.560
can get certain preferences.

01:15:51.100 --> 01:15:52.760
And now before the accession,

01:15:52.770 --> 01:15:54.240
it must agree on what level

01:15:54.250 --> 01:15:56.820
to fix the same protective barriers

01:15:56.830 --> 01:15:58.760
in order that agriculture in

01:15:58.770 --> 01:16:01.120
Russia is sufficiently well

01:16:01.130 --> 01:16:05.520
protected and entitled to subsidies.

01:16:06.880 --> 01:16:08.540
The next aspect, which was linked

01:16:08.550 --> 01:16:10.900
to the new GAD 1994 edition,

01:16:10.910 --> 01:16:13.040
is anti-dumping measures.

01:16:13.050 --> 01:16:15.660
In this regard, Russia has made

01:16:15.670 --> 01:16:17.400
a great progress, because in the

01:16:17.410 --> 01:16:21.080
new XXI century anti-dumping legislation

01:16:21.090 --> 01:16:22.820
and various regulatory

01:16:22.830 --> 01:16:25.880
acts were adopted that regulate,

01:16:25.890 --> 01:16:28.040
so to speak, the rules of

01:16:28.050 --> 01:16:30.700
recognition of dumping on the

01:16:30.710 --> 01:16:33.320
territory of Russia and the introduction

01:16:33.330 --> 01:16:36.820
of anti-dumping sanctions.

01:16:37.340 --> 01:16:40.100
I have already said that Russian

01:16:40.110 --> 01:16:43.540
export flows are quite strongly limited

01:16:43.550 --> 01:16:46.760
in different directions, and

01:16:46.770 --> 01:16:48.780
not only in the direction of the United

01:16:48.790 --> 01:16:50.440
States and Western Europe,

01:16:50.450 --> 01:16:53.020
but even in the direction of the

01:16:53.030 --> 01:16:55.100
Asian region, to new developed

01:16:55.110 --> 01:16:56.020
countries.

01:16:56.060 --> 01:16:59.180
Once the countries have been

01:16:59.190 --> 01:17:01.480
able to develop their heavy industry

01:17:01.490 --> 01:17:03.880
thoroughly enough, obstacles are

01:17:03.890 --> 01:17:06.200
set and proved by the dumping

01:17:06.210 --> 01:17:08.420
situation on, for example,

01:17:08.860 --> 01:17:10.980
Russian goods, in particular,

01:17:10.990 --> 01:17:13.500
metal production.

01:17:14.940 --> 01:17:16.720
Now, of course, in general, in connection

01:17:16.730 --> 01:17:20.040
with the rise of world prices

01:17:20.050 --> 01:17:21.920
for various commodity-intensive

01:17:21.930 --> 01:17:24.360
goods, which are the main component

01:17:24.370 --> 01:17:26.120
of Russian exports, such

01:17:26.130 --> 01:17:30.300
dumping claims from buyers,

01:17:30.310 --> 01:17:33.020
these countries-importers are

01:17:33.030 --> 01:17:35.780
coming to Russia less and less.

01:17:36.600 --> 01:17:38.700
This is due to the fact that, for example,

01:17:38.860 --> 01:17:41.680
mostly disputes with Russia

01:17:41.690 --> 01:17:45.940
about dumping were from the 90s to 95s.

01:17:46.020 --> 01:17:48.040
It was during this period that Russia

01:17:48.050 --> 01:17:50.260
was accused of a fairly large

01:17:50.270 --> 01:17:53.240
number of dumping charges, and it

01:17:53.250 --> 01:17:56.080
was ignored that the country at

01:17:56.090 --> 01:17:58.880
that time was no longer a centralized

01:17:58.890 --> 01:18:00.940
socialist economy, and indeed

01:18:00.950 --> 01:18:02.160
the exporters used some

01:18:02.170 --> 01:18:03.680
of their specific advantages

01:18:03.690 --> 01:18:05.800
associated with cheap

01:18:05.810 --> 01:18:07.640
raw materials of cheap

01:18:07.650 --> 01:18:09.000
labor.

01:18:09.010 --> 01:18:11.420
