01:47:31.980 --> 01:47:34.810
trade with the European Union, it was

01:47:34.820 --> 01:47:37.870
the representatives of the European

01:47:37.880 --> 01:47:40.970
Union that were entrusted with the

01:47:40.980 --> 01:47:44.530
preparation of these very requirements

01:47:44.540 --> 01:47:47.210
and conditions for Russia's accession

01:47:47.220 --> 01:47:48.910
to the ETO.

01:47:49.630 --> 01:47:54.630
In 1998, the initial proposals

01:47:54.640 --> 01:47:57.950
on access to the market of goods

01:47:57.960 --> 01:48:03.010
and services and on the level of

01:48:03.020 --> 01:48:06.490
support for agriculture from

01:48:08.760 --> 01:48:12.530
Russia and member countries

01:48:12.540 --> 01:48:15.010
began.

01:48:16.410 --> 01:48:18.330
And these initial proposals,

01:48:18.340 --> 01:48:20.170
again, were adjusted

01:48:20.180 --> 01:48:22.090
for a long time, almost

01:48:22.330 --> 01:48:24.450
for two years.

01:48:25.010 --> 01:48:26.890
And, in fact, only from the beginning

01:48:26.900 --> 01:48:29.610
of the new millennium in 2000 began

01:48:29.620 --> 01:48:32.310
to be discussed all aspects of the

01:48:32.320 --> 01:48:34.490
process of accession of Russia to

01:48:34.500 --> 01:48:35.830
the World Trade Organization,

01:48:35.840 --> 01:48:41.150
and not only the problems related to

01:48:41.160 --> 01:48:44.150
the agreement between GAD and GAC.

01:48:44.590 --> 01:48:46.270
What is the state of the modern

01:48:46.280 --> 01:48:49.510
working group, which conducts, analyzes,

01:48:49.520 --> 01:48:51.170
makes decisions, analyzes the

01:48:51.210 --> 01:48:53.490
problems related to the accession

01:48:53.500 --> 01:48:54.850
of Russia to the ETO?

01:48:55.670 --> 01:48:59.010
First of all, according to the requirements

01:48:59.020 --> 01:49:00.750
of the ETO, the standard requirements

01:49:00.760 --> 01:49:03.430
for all potential members of the ETO,

01:49:03.440 --> 01:49:04.950
this group includes, of course, not all

01:49:04.960 --> 01:49:07.850
150 countries, representatives of

01:49:07.860 --> 01:49:11.990
not all 150 countries of the

01:49:12.000 --> 01:49:14.270
world, namely those countries

01:49:14.280 --> 01:49:16.410
that maintain the closest foreign

01:49:16.420 --> 01:49:19.290
trade relations with a potential member,

01:49:20.170 --> 01:49:23.070
and precisely those countries that,

01:49:23.080 --> 01:49:24.830
so to speak, have some

01:49:24.840 --> 01:49:28.130
unsatisfied issues in conducting

01:49:28.140 --> 01:49:32.310
this very foreign trade.

01:49:43.890 --> 01:49:47.610
And so until the end of 2006 in such

01:49:48.530 --> 01:49:50.590
blocs was considered as one

01:49:50.600 --> 01:49:51.850
country.

01:49:52.470 --> 01:49:54.450
Therefore, 58 countries are a large

01:49:54.460 --> 01:49:56.150
group of countries, which include

01:49:56.160 --> 01:49:57.830
not only developed countries but also

01:49:57.840 --> 01:50:00.030
developing countries, which are

01:50:00.040 --> 01:50:02.110
interested in the Russian market or

01:50:02.120 --> 01:50:05.950
in the import of products,

01:50:05.960 --> 01:50:07.490
Russian products or from

01:50:07.500 --> 01:50:08.450
Russian territory.

01:50:09.250 --> 01:50:13.010
In early 2007, Vietnam

01:50:13.020 --> 01:50:14.670
and Cambodia joined

01:50:14.680 --> 01:50:16.970
the negotiations.

01:50:17.250 --> 01:50:19.290
What could this be related to?

01:50:19.350 --> 01:50:21.950
First, Vietnam and Cambodia

01:50:21.960 --> 01:50:24.810
are large agricultural

01:50:24.820 --> 01:50:27.110
producers.

01:50:27.310 --> 01:50:28.970
On the other hand, Vietnam has

01:50:28.980 --> 01:50:32.510
recently tried to intercept the world

01:50:32.520 --> 01:50:36.070
factory squad from China.

01:50:36.130 --> 01:50:37.950
That is, on the territory of Vietnam

01:50:37.960 --> 01:50:39.310
is organized

01:50:41.050 --> 01:50:41.970
export-oriented production,

01:50:41.980 --> 01:50:45.170
quite cheap products related

01:50:45.180 --> 01:50:48.630
to clothing, with the assembly

01:50:48.640 --> 01:50:52.770
of some final consumption goods.

01:50:53.310 --> 01:50:55.870
They joined the negotiation process

01:50:55.880 --> 01:50:58.090
in 2007 because the issues

01:50:58.100 --> 01:50:59.950
of barriers to agricultural

01:50:59.960 --> 01:51:03.230
products are being

01:51:03.910 --> 01:51:05.750
resolved right now.

01:51:05.990 --> 01:51:08.110
The number of working

01:51:08.120 --> 01:51:10.470
groups that are working

01:51:10.480 --> 01:51:13.030
on Russia's accession

01:51:13.040 --> 01:51:16.010
to the WTO is now

01:51:16.020 --> 01:51:17.130
500.

01:51:18.610 --> 01:51:23.810
It is 50 member countries.

01:51:23.820 --> 01:51:25.410
These are the countries that

01:51:25.430 --> 01:51:28.670
are primarily interested

01:51:28.680 --> 01:51:31.570
in regulating trade.

01:51:31.990 --> 01:51:33.650
In terms of access to

01:51:33.660 --> 01:51:36.370
the Russian market, the group

01:51:36.380 --> 01:51:38.270
has about 30 members.

01:51:38.470 --> 01:51:44.250
If we summarize the situation

01:51:45.430 --> 01:51:47.250
of the negotiation process

01:51:47.260 --> 01:51:50.110
now, we can highlight the

01:51:50.120 --> 01:51:52.710
following elements of this

01:51:52.720 --> 01:51:54.710
negotiation process, which

01:51:54.720 --> 01:51:57.890
took place in 2007.

01:51:58.270 --> 01:52:00.930
First of all, the level of binding

01:52:00.940 --> 01:52:04.030
of the rates of roaming duties

01:52:04.040 --> 01:52:07.870
on Russian territory is currently determined.

01:52:07.880 --> 01:52:09.490
What is the level of connection?

01:52:09.510 --> 01:52:11.910
That is, the maximum interest rate

01:52:11.920 --> 01:52:15.390
for different product groups

01:52:15.400 --> 01:52:17.990
is determined, which will be

01:52:18.000 --> 01:52:20.810
retained after Russia joins all

01:52:22.380 --> 01:52:31.230
members of the working group.

01:52:31.240 --> 01:52:34.110
They agreed that the initial level

01:52:34.120 --> 01:52:35.670
of bonding of customs duties

01:52:35.680 --> 01:52:39.650
would not be lower than the current level.

01:52:40.210 --> 01:52:42.290
In the first year,

01:52:42.300 --> 01:52:44.030
no tariffs will be

01:52:44.040 --> 01:52:45.030
reduced.

01:52:46.130 --> 01:52:47.870
The level of customs protection

01:52:47.880 --> 01:52:50.090
of agriculture will not decrease, and

01:52:50.100 --> 01:52:54.030
in a number of positions Russia

01:52:54.040 --> 01:52:56.430
even has the right to raise the

01:52:56.440 --> 01:52:58.810
rates of customs duties a bit in

01:52:58.820 --> 01:53:00.470
this very transitional period

01:53:00.480 --> 01:53:02.750
until 2009.

01:53:03.650 --> 01:53:08.770
In 2009, the right to use tariff

01:53:08.780 --> 01:53:12.170
quotas for three types of meat was

01:53:12.180 --> 01:53:14.370
recorded - beef, pork and poultry

01:53:14.380 --> 01:53:15.570
meat.

01:53:16.210 --> 01:53:20.590
The technology for determining these

01:53:20.600 --> 01:53:23.310
quotas is the current level of

01:53:23.320 --> 01:53:28.390
quotas plus 2.5 percent expansion of

01:53:28.400 --> 01:53:31.550
quotas depending on the annual

01:53:31.560 --> 01:53:36.330
growth of the supply of meat production

01:53:36.340 --> 01:53:39.190
on Russian territory.

01:53:39.890 --> 01:53:45.230
You know that 2006-2007 was marked by quite

01:53:45.240 --> 01:53:48.010
thunderstorm disputes between the European

01:53:48.020 --> 01:53:50.750
Union and, in particular, Poland

01:53:50.760 --> 01:53:52.950
over the embargo on meat imports

01:53:52.960 --> 01:53:57.690
from the territory of the European Union.

01:53:57.730 --> 01:53:59.030
Not only from the territory of Poland,

01:53:59.040 --> 01:54:00.910
but a number of countries are included

01:54:00.920 --> 01:54:01.950
in this list.

01:54:02.390 --> 01:54:06.350
It is in connection with the fact that, in

01:54:06.360 --> 01:54:07.890
the opinion of the Russian country,

01:54:07.900 --> 01:54:10.570
certain technical, so to speak, medical

01:54:10.580 --> 01:54:14.090
requirements and standards have been violated.

01:54:15.110 --> 01:54:18.870
In the future, as you can see, Russia

01:54:18.880 --> 01:54:21.010
has at least at this stage of negotiations

01:54:21.020 --> 01:54:23.930
obtained the right to maintain

01:54:23.940 --> 01:54:25.430
such protectionist

01:54:25.440 --> 01:54:28.090
measures with regard to meat

01:54:28.100 --> 01:54:31.090
imports.

01:54:33.190 --> 01:54:36.210
In general, for example, the second

01:54:36.220 --> 01:54:38.650
significant direction of negotiations,

01:54:38.660 --> 01:54:40.510
negotiations on agricultural

01:54:40.520 --> 01:54:42.870
issues, came to the fact that Russia'

01:54:43.510 --> 01:54:47.890
s position has not yet been recognized,

01:54:47.900 --> 01:54:51.750
it is not agreed on the part of

01:54:51.760 --> 01:54:56.390
the party to accept the proposal

01:54:56.410 --> 01:54:58.690
that Russia made for negotiations.

01:54:58.700 --> 01:55:02.270
Russia proposes to fix the amount

01:55:02.280 --> 01:55:04.130
of support for our agriculture

01:55:04.140 --> 01:55:07.050
in the reserve period

01:55:07.060 --> 01:55:12.870
1993-1995.

01:55:14.390 --> 01:55:18.430
The amount of support will

01:55:18.440 --> 01:55:22.050
be $9.5 billion a year, but,

01:55:22.540 --> 01:55:26.990
it would seem, such a not so

01:55:27.000 --> 01:55:28.870
large amount compared to

01:55:28.880 --> 01:55:30.950
the EU's investments in

01:55:30.960 --> 01:55:33.850
its agriculture has not yet

01:55:33.860 --> 01:55:36.490
been perceived by the negotiating

01:55:36.500 --> 01:55:40.970
parties as a normal level

01:55:40.980 --> 01:55:43.670
of protectionist protection

01:55:43.680 --> 01:55:46.090
in the form of state

01:55:46.100 --> 01:55:48.270
subsidies for agriculture,

01:55:48.280 --> 01:55:51.770
export or national economy.

01:55:52.830 --> 01:55:57.030
The allowed amount of domestic state

01:55:57.230 --> 01:56:00.070
support of the agricultural sector,

01:56:00.930 --> 01:56:02.750
of course, does not apply to all

01:56:02.760 --> 01:56:05.350
types of agricultural products,

01:56:05.360 --> 01:56:07.370
but only a certain list, the so-

01:56:07.380 --> 01:56:09.190
called yellow basket.

01:56:15.130 --> 01:56:17.490
This list includes the product

01:56:17.500 --> 01:56:19.770
demanding a reduction

01:56:19.780 --> 01:56:21.730
in protectionism.

01:56:24.540 --> 01:56:26.640
The next, third block is

01:56:26.650 --> 01:56:31.500
the access to the service market.

01:56:31.920 --> 01:56:34.260
This is primarily financial

01:56:35.340 --> 01:56:38.200
services and energy

01:56:39.080 --> 01:56:40.700
services.

01:56:41.260 --> 01:56:45.100
And in this regard, of course,

01:56:45.380 --> 01:56:48.280
the struggle is due to the fact

01:56:48.290 --> 01:56:51.580
that restricting access to the service

01:56:51.590 --> 01:56:56.100
market is lobbied by our financial groups,

01:56:56.360 --> 01:56:59.140
and they prove that access to the

01:56:59.150 --> 01:57:00.920
financial market, which is not

01:57:00.930 --> 01:57:03.120
yet so sustainable, they think

01:57:03.620 --> 01:57:04.980
should be limited.

01:57:05.180 --> 01:57:06.480
Consequently, in the process of

01:57:06.490 --> 01:57:10.860
negotiations these problems are raised.

01:57:11.700 --> 01:57:13.740
The next sector is not only

01:57:13.750 --> 01:57:15.860
financial, but also energy.

01:57:16.760 --> 01:57:19.740
And here India advocates for access

01:57:19.750 --> 01:57:22.040
to individuals.

01:57:22.050 --> 01:57:23.600
India, Canada and Switzerland

01:57:23.610 --> 01:57:26.580
are advocating for individuals' access

01:57:26.590 --> 01:57:30.840
to the Russian market in

01:57:30.850 --> 01:57:34.540
certain sectors of financial services.

01:57:35.460 --> 01:57:38.160
In principle, the negotiators concluded

01:57:38.170 --> 01:57:41.440
that Russia agreed to open

01:57:41.450 --> 01:57:45.220
115 services sectors out of

01:57:45.230 --> 01:57:49.120
the 150 sectors listed by

01:57:49.130 --> 01:57:52.980
the World Trade Organization.

01:57:53.220 --> 01:58:01.580
The proposal also stipulates the

01:58:01.590 --> 01:58:03.600
stricter conditions for foreign

01:58:03.610 --> 01:58:08.220
service providers on the Russian market.

01:58:08.620 --> 01:58:12.260
And the next block, the last block,

01:58:12.720 --> 01:58:15.360
concerning the negotiation process

01:58:15.370 --> 01:58:17.780
is negotiations on systemic issues.

01:58:17.980 --> 01:58:19.320
This is primarily

01:58:19.330 --> 01:58:21.020
the Russian law.

01:58:21.460 --> 01:58:25.420
Three blocks of questions are raised.

01:58:25.540 --> 01:58:27.280
The first is the non-compliance

01:58:27.290 --> 01:58:28.880
of Russian legislation with the

01:58:30.520 --> 01:58:32.920
WTO requirement in the field

01:58:32.930 --> 01:58:34.220
of sanitary and phytosanitary

01:58:34.230 --> 01:58:35.720
measures.

01:58:36.220 --> 01:58:37.840
Basically, we have raised these questions

01:58:37.850 --> 01:58:39.760
with you already.

01:58:40.100 --> 01:58:42.060
And this includes not only various

01:58:42.070 --> 01:58:44.200
tariff quotas for meat, but also,

01:58:44.210 --> 01:58:46.960
as the WTO working group believes,

01:58:46.970 --> 01:58:49.380
excessive requirements for alcohol

01:58:49.390 --> 01:58:51.360
and pharmaceuticals.

01:58:52.160 --> 01:58:53.440
As you can see, the

01:58:53.450 --> 01:58:56.700
country that is interested

01:58:56.710 --> 01:58:58.580
here is India.

01:58:59.020 --> 01:59:04.920
The next direction is the

01:59:04.930 --> 01:59:09.000
use of some elements of state

01:59:09.010 --> 01:59:10.040
regulation in the sphere

01:59:10.050 --> 01:59:11.660
of foreign economic

01:59:11.670 --> 01:59:13.940
activity, which, again, do

01:59:14.160 --> 01:59:15.580
not meet the requirements

01:59:15.590 --> 01:59:17.280
and standards of the

01:59:17.290 --> 01:59:19.480
World Trade Organization.

01:59:19.780 --> 01:59:21.940
The last block – requirements on systemic

01:59:21.950 --> 01:59:24.880
issues, changes in the legal

01:59:24.890 --> 01:59:26.300
system of Russia, are called

01:59:26.820 --> 01:59:28.200
the WTO+.

01:59:28.210 --> 01:59:30.360
In principle, of course, Russia may

01:59:30.370 --> 01:59:31.700
not pay attention to them because

01:59:31.920 --> 01:59:34.520
they are not within the jurisdiction

01:59:34.530 --> 01:59:38.100
of the World Trade Organization.

01:59:38.680 --> 01:59:40.240
They are related to government procurement

01:59:40.250 --> 01:59:42.940
of civil aviation equipment.

01:59:43.420 --> 01:59:46.000
However, in order to eliminate possible

01:59:46.010 --> 01:59:48.740
conflicts and subsequent problems

01:59:48.750 --> 01:59:50.860
with the situation in trade flows,

01:59:50.870 --> 01:59:55.080
these negotiations also take place.

01:59:56.640 --> 01:59:58.360
What other requirements do WTO member

01:59:58.370 --> 02:00:00.320
countries make to Russia in the

02:00:00.330 --> 02:00:02.820
framework of mutual agreements?

02:00:03.160 --> 02:00:05.380
This is the abolition of the

02:00:05.390 --> 02:00:07.580
national components of investment projects.

02:00:08.360 --> 02:00:11.480
For now, it was assumed that when

02:00:11.490 --> 02:00:15.040
direct investments are made in the

02:00:16.710 --> 02:00:23.620
Russian market, the national

02:00:23.630 --> 02:00:25.800
component should also be

02:00:25.810 --> 02:00:28.920
included in the investment process.

02:00:29.840 --> 02:00:32.300
The next requirement is to ensure

02:00:32.310 --> 02:00:33.860
compliance with the requirements

02:00:33.870 --> 02:00:35.540
of the WTO, the applicable tariff

02:00:35.550 --> 02:00:37.340
quotas.

02:00:37.440 --> 02:00:39.020
This applies to agricultural

02:00:39.030 --> 02:00:41.160
agreements.

02:00:41.600 --> 02:00:44.620
This requirement involves

02:00:44.630 --> 02:00:45.960
such agreements that

02:00:45.970 --> 02:00:47.620
reduce their use.

02:00:49.760 --> 02:00:52.000
The next requirement is the

02:00:52.010 --> 02:00:53.940
organization of the transactions

02:00:53.950 --> 02:00:55.220
of sale by state trade

02:00:55.480 --> 02:00:59.660
enterprises on a commercial basis.

02:00:59.760 --> 02:01:02.460
The most important requirement is not to

02:01:02.470 --> 02:01:06.140
discriminate against foreign companies in participating

02:01:06.150 --> 02:01:08.560
in these transactions.

02:01:09.220 --> 02:01:11.820
This component is due to the fact

02:01:11.830 --> 02:01:14.680
that in developed countries

02:01:14.690 --> 02:01:18.480
the state distributes

02:01:18.490 --> 02:01:22.680
state orders among domestic producers.

02:01:23.900 --> 02:01:25.900
But within these crossings, it

02:01:25.910 --> 02:01:28.080
is expected that a consensus

02:01:28.090 --> 02:01:31.120
will be developed that will allow

02:01:31.130 --> 02:01:34.240
foreign companies to participate

02:01:34.250 --> 02:01:36.760
in purchasing programs to

02:01:36.770 --> 02:01:39.420
a greater extent.

02:01:39.460 --> 02:01:42.180
The last essential requirement

02:01:42.190 --> 02:01:43.720
put forward by the

02:01:43.730 --> 02:01:46.000
WTO members is the question

02:01:46.010 --> 02:01:47.780
of dual education on

02:01:47.790 --> 02:01:49.440
energy goods.

02:01:49.800 --> 02:01:51.580
This question is quite complex.

02:01:51.880 --> 02:01:55.160
Here, Russia has developed a

02:01:55.170 --> 02:01:58.120
tough position, showing that

02:01:58.130 --> 02:02:01.180
we, with our energy goods,

02:02:01.190 --> 02:02:04.420
energy donors in certain volumes,

02:02:04.430 --> 02:02:06.800
at certain stable

02:02:06.810 --> 02:02:08.320
prices, must provide

02:02:08.330 --> 02:02:11.560
national demand of national

02:02:11.570 --> 02:02:13.700
producers.

02:02:14.560 --> 02:02:17.280
Now we will consider the last question

02:02:17.290 --> 02:02:20.420
of our lecture, concerning

02:02:20.430 --> 02:02:23.360
the readiness of the Russian

02:02:23.370 --> 02:02:24.820
market of Russian producers

02:02:24.830 --> 02:02:25.840
to join the WTO.

02:02:26.900 --> 02:02:29.180
On the one hand, Russian producers

02:02:29.190 --> 02:02:31.560
were protected from foreign flow of

02:02:31.570 --> 02:02:35.380
goods and services at the expense

02:02:35.390 --> 02:02:38.500
of the currency component almost

02:02:38.510 --> 02:02:42.920
in the period after the 1998 crisis.

02:02:43.460 --> 02:02:45.220
We have been aware of the situation

02:02:45.230 --> 02:02:47.620
in international economic relations

02:02:47.630 --> 02:02:50.360
where the exchange rate

02:02:50.370 --> 02:02:51.900
can act as a protectionist

02:02:51.910 --> 02:02:53.500
barrier.

02:02:53.900 --> 02:02:55.760
If the ruble is weak enough,

02:02:55.770 --> 02:02:58.260
it means that you can buy a

02:02:58.270 --> 02:03:01.400
smaller amount of dollars

02:03:01.410 --> 02:03:03.480
or euros for this ruble and,

02:03:03.490 --> 02:03:07.080
accordingly, a smaller

02:03:07.090 --> 02:03:10.620
amount of goods for imports.

02:03:10.660 --> 02:03:16.920
By 2001, this currency protectionism

02:03:16.930 --> 02:03:20.680
was exhausted.

02:03:20.760 --> 02:03:22.940
Based on this, starting in 2001,

02:03:22.950 --> 02:03:25.420
pay attention to the scheme, in general,

02:03:26.440 --> 02:03:30.180
the Russian manufacturer

02:03:30.190 --> 02:03:32.100
has already been in a situation

02:03:32.110 --> 02:03:33.940
of normal competitiveness,

02:03:35.770 --> 02:03:37.560
and the competition

02:03:37.570 --> 02:03:39.440
of imports from far abroad

02:03:39.450 --> 02:03:41.860
in this case has increased.

02:03:41.960 --> 02:03:43.380
This is not a new revelation

02:03:43.390 --> 02:03:45.840
for the Russian manufacturers.

02:03:46.880 --> 02:03:50.580
The Russian ruble is still

02:03:50.590 --> 02:03:52.700
stable and has a certain

02:03:52.710 --> 02:03:56.360
growth rate.

02:03:56.680 --> 02:03:58.820
But here everything depends on

02:03:58.830 --> 02:04:00.980
the central bank's monetary policy,

02:04:01.280 --> 02:04:03.880
to what extent it will be acceptable

02:04:03.890 --> 02:04:07.120
for the Russian economy to deliberately

02:04:07.130 --> 02:04:09.820
intervene to reduce the currency

02:04:09.830 --> 02:04:12.080
rate of the ruble.

02:04:12.090 --> 02:04:14.740
Such an automatic mechanism, which

02:04:14.750 --> 02:04:19.560
was associated with the weak

02:04:19.570 --> 02:04:21.000
national Russian currency ruble,

02:04:21.010 --> 02:04:24.820
is in this case already exhausted.

02:04:25.600 --> 02:04:27.900
And for the past 5-6 years, Russian

02:04:27.910 --> 02:04:31.700
manufacturers have been forced

02:04:31.710 --> 02:04:33.680
to take this into account.

02:04:36.380 --> 02:04:39.480
Pay attention to Russia's import

02:04:39.490 --> 02:04:47.040
tariffs and the strange members

02:04:47.050 --> 02:04:49.740
of the conciliation group

02:04:49.750 --> 02:04:53.140
demanding the removal of

02:04:53.150 --> 02:04:55.040
some protectionist restrictions

02:04:55.050 --> 02:04:56.200
on agriculture.

02:04:56.900 --> 02:05:00.540
Our tariffs are quite comparable

02:05:00.550 --> 02:05:03.420
to the restrictions currently in force

02:05:03.430 --> 02:05:05.560
in the territory of developed

02:05:05.570 --> 02:05:07.520
and developing countries.

02:05:08.220 --> 02:05:10.700
In developing countries,

02:05:10.840 --> 02:05:13.600
tariffs on agricultural

02:05:13.610 --> 02:05:15.300
imports reach

02:05:15.780 --> 02:05:19.440
almost 19%.

02:05:19.450 --> 02:05:23.260
In a large export and import economy

02:05:23.270 --> 02:05:24.960
like China, this is even

02:05:25.300 --> 02:05:26.940
40%.

02:05:26.950 --> 02:05:29.880
In countries with transitional economies,

02:05:29.890 --> 02:05:34.240
this percentage is quite high and

02:05:34.250 --> 02:05:36.920
reaches about 16%.

02:05:36.930 --> 02:05:40.420
In developed countries, the national

02:05:40.430 --> 02:05:42.960
agricultural market

02:05:42.970 --> 02:05:43.680
protection

02:05:43.690 --> 02:05:45.600
is sufficiently strong.

02:05:45.700 --> 02:05:47.420
As you know, this is the main

02:05:47.430 --> 02:05:48.980
problem in the negotiations between

02:05:48.990 --> 02:05:50.900
the EU and the United States, in the

02:05:50.910 --> 02:05:53.320
negotiations between the EU and

02:05:53.330 --> 02:05:54.580
developing countries.

02:05:54.740 --> 02:05:57.560
The EU has raised the protectionist

02:05:57.570 --> 02:06:00.320
protection in agriculture

02:06:00.330 --> 02:06:02.760
to 43.4%.

02:06:02.770 --> 02:06:05.320


02:06:05.330 --> 02:06:09.640
There is a prohibitive level

02:06:09.650 --> 02:06:12.180
of tariffs.

02:06:13.020 --> 02:06:15.360
And based on these figures, we

02:06:15.370 --> 02:06:17.300
can say that our domestic agriculture

02:06:17.310 --> 02:06:19.060
and agricultural producers

02:06:19.070 --> 02:06:20.780
already operate within the framework

02:06:20.790 --> 02:06:23.100
of a sufficiently liberalized

02:06:23.110 --> 02:06:24.940
market for agricultural

02:06:24.950 --> 02:06:26.560
products.

02:06:26.880 --> 02:06:28.900
Therefore, accession to

02:06:28.910 --> 02:06:30.540
the WTO whileining this

02:06:30.550 --> 02:06:32.980
level of protection for a transitional

02:06:32.990 --> 02:06:34.740
period, or even a decrease

02:06:34.750 --> 02:06:37.020
at a certain stage of this

02:06:37.030 --> 02:06:40.380
level, will not lead to

02:06:40.390 --> 02:06:42.000
some unexpected results

02:06:42.010 --> 02:06:44.160
for agricultural producers.

02:06:44.900 --> 02:06:46.540
Pay attention to the slide,

02:06:46.820 --> 02:06:48.540
which illustrates the actual level

02:06:48.550 --> 02:06:52.100
of import, import tariff.

02:06:52.440 --> 02:06:55.780
If we consider that the so-called

02:06:55.790 --> 02:06:58.460
weighted average rate of the import

02:06:58.470 --> 02:06:59.960
tariff is usually calculated in

02:06:59.970 --> 02:07:01.760
international debates and calculations,

02:07:01.770 --> 02:07:04.740
then by 2000, gradually decreasing,

02:07:04.750 --> 02:07:06.540
it reached an average of 2.5% in

02:07:06.550 --> 02:07:08.820
our country.

02:07:08.830 --> 02:07:11.100
Of course, this average is quite

02:07:11.110 --> 02:07:14.360
conditional, because it is calculated

02:07:14.370 --> 02:07:16.300
as a kind of average temperature

02:07:16.310 --> 02:07:17.940
for the hospital.

02:07:18.040 --> 02:07:20.700
That is, one has a limit temperature,

02:07:20.710 --> 02:07:22.880
and the other, unfortunately,

02:07:22.890 --> 02:07:25.160
already. So, the weighted

02:07:25.380 --> 02:07:27.360
average rate is, I repeat,

02:07:27.370 --> 02:07:29.080
now already by 2000,

02:07:29.380 --> 02:07:31.580
and now is still slightly

02:07:31.590 --> 02:07:34.360
below 12.5%.

02:07:34.370 --> 02:07:36.420
But an effective rate of the

02:07:36.430 --> 02:07:38.640
import tariff implies that we also

02:07:38.880 --> 02:07:43.800
take into account the flows associated

02:07:43.810 --> 02:07:46.800
with the shadow economy and other

02:07:46.810 --> 02:07:53.740
negative protection of the

02:07:53.750 --> 02:07:55.720
existing tariff.

02:07:55.730 --> 02:07:58.260
In this case, the effective

02:07:58.270 --> 02:08:00.300
rate of the import

02:08:00.310 --> 02:08:02.520
tariff is only about

02:08:02.530 --> 02:08:04.640
9%.

02:08:04.650 --> 02:08:08.060
Thus, the Russian market, I repeat,

02:08:08.070 --> 02:08:10.560
has already used to working

02:08:10.570 --> 02:08:13.300
in fairly tough conditions

02:08:13.310 --> 02:08:15.980
of competitive struggle with imports.

02:08:17.540 --> 02:08:20.300
The Russian proposals on the part

02:08:20.310 --> 02:08:21.540
of the Russian delegation

02:08:21.550 --> 02:08:25.500
to the negotiations include expanding

02:08:25.510 --> 02:08:29.280
the corridor of protectionist rates

02:08:29.290 --> 02:08:31.120
and fixing the initial and

02:08:31.130 --> 02:08:33.700
final level of the related tariff

02:08:33.710 --> 02:08:35.220
bond, i.e. the upper and lower

02:08:35.230 --> 02:08:37.320
limit of the tariff,

02:08:37.330 --> 02:08:40.300
on industrial goods at the level

02:08:40.310 --> 02:08:47.020
of 14.3% to 9.8%, against

02:08:47.030 --> 02:08:52.760
the real level of 9.7% of the

02:08:52.770 --> 02:08:55.480
average tariff.

02:08:57.320 --> 02:09:00.820
What are the real factors

02:09:00.830 --> 02:09:02.260
of open economy?

02:09:02.700 --> 02:09:06.060
Of course, these are factors that are

02:09:06.070 --> 02:09:08.960
contrary to the normal operation of economic

02:09:08.970 --> 02:09:12.420
policy, which is developed and

02:09:12.430 --> 02:09:14.800
in accordance with our legislation.

02:09:16.120 --> 02:09:20.220
First, on the one hand, these are

02:09:20.230 --> 02:09:22.900
such negative factors as the

02:09:22.910 --> 02:09:26.020
existence of gray schemes, when

02:09:26.030 --> 02:09:28.960
goods produced and designed

02:09:28.970 --> 02:09:30.960
for lower income of the population,

02:09:30.970 --> 02:09:32.360
oriented to some third

02:09:32.400 --> 02:09:33.780
of developing countries, fall

02:09:33.790 --> 02:09:35.780
on the Russian market and,

02:09:35.790 --> 02:09:37.000
accordingly, they

02:09:37.010 --> 02:09:39.240
are in relation to our goods

02:09:39.250 --> 02:09:41.160
in essence sold and offered

02:09:41.170 --> 02:09:45.160
under dumping schemes.

02:09:45.170 --> 02:09:47.480
On the other hand, importers have

02:09:47.490 --> 02:09:50.480
serious schemes of tax optimization,

02:09:50.490 --> 02:09:52.840
which also lowers the price

02:09:52.850 --> 02:09:56.360
level of imported goods.

02:09:56.640 --> 02:09:59.280
The last negative component is the

02:09:59.290 --> 02:10:02.920
boat imports, which have recently

02:10:02.930 --> 02:10:04.100
been somewhat reduced, as

02:10:04.110 --> 02:10:07.060
such competition in the Russian

02:10:07.070 --> 02:10:09.600
market, the growth of Russian population's

02:10:09.720 --> 02:10:13.620
income and the increase of the bar

02:10:13.630 --> 02:10:17.620
of requirements for product quality

02:10:17.630 --> 02:10:19.660
leads to the fact that gradually

02:10:19.670 --> 02:10:21.420
boat imports are collapsing

02:10:21.430 --> 02:10:23.700
and becoming more organized

02:10:23.710 --> 02:10:25.840
at the level of small and

02:10:25.850 --> 02:10:28.200
medium-sized importers.

02:10:28.720 --> 02:10:30.760
The next factor, which is no longer related

02:10:30.770 --> 02:10:32.400
to the shadow economy and, in principle,

02:10:32.410 --> 02:10:34.880
is subject to possible regulation

02:10:34.890 --> 02:10:36.080
by the government in the

02:10:36.090 --> 02:10:38.040
person of the Central Bank, is the

02:10:38.600 --> 02:10:40.300
rise of the ruble.

02:10:40.380 --> 02:10:43.400
As I said, a stronger and more stable

02:10:43.410 --> 02:10:45.540
ruble, but with a tendency

02:10:45.550 --> 02:10:47.720
to rise, usually restricts

02:10:47.730 --> 02:10:50.500
exports and increases imports.

02:10:51.200 --> 02:10:54.920
This factor has been working

02:10:54.930 --> 02:10:57.720
for a year, at least since 2002,

02:10:57.730 --> 02:11:01.300
and, accordingly, Russian manufacturers

02:11:01.310 --> 02:11:03.320
should have become

02:11:03.330 --> 02:11:08.620
accustomed to this factor too.

02:11:08.630 --> 02:11:12.080
In the case of gray imports, I would like

02:11:12.090 --> 02:11:14.540
to draw your attention to the fact that,

02:11:14.550 --> 02:11:19.440
according to the calculations of independent

02:11:19.450 --> 02:11:23.400
organizations, for the six months

02:11:23.410 --> 02:11:25.300
of 2006, gray imports amounted

02:11:25.310 --> 02:11:27.760
to a fairly serious amount,

02:11:27.770 --> 02:11:33.300
which reached $18 billion.

02:11:36.400 --> 02:11:40.440
However, this type of imports

02:11:40.450 --> 02:11:45.360
may decrease.

02:11:45.740 --> 02:11:52.540
Because, if in 2005, gray imports

02:11:52.550 --> 02:11:54.340
worked, the development of modern

02:11:54.350 --> 02:11:56.520
legislation and adaptation to

02:11:56.530 --> 02:11:58.280
the WTO rules leads to the

02:11:58.290 --> 02:11:59.840
fact that gray imports are slightly

02:11:59.850 --> 02:12:05.420
reduced from 47% to 32%.

02:12:05.430 --> 02:12:07.920
True, the Central Bank gives lower figures,

02:12:07.930 --> 02:12:10.600
in fact, twice the case, but in this

02:12:10.610 --> 02:12:13.760
case we will consider that the

02:12:13.770 --> 02:12:15.700
truth is somewhere in the

02:12:15.710 --> 02:12:17.900
middle between the expert assessment

02:12:17.910 --> 02:12:20.480
of specialists and the calculations

02:12:20.490 --> 02:12:22.580
of the Central Bank.

02:12:22.590 --> 02:12:24.760
The last thing I would like to

02:12:24.770 --> 02:12:27.580
draw your attention to is that,

02:12:27.590 --> 02:12:30.640
based on the previous slide scheme,

02:12:30.860 --> 02:12:33.040
we have in general already in the

02:12:33.050 --> 02:12:36.540
Russian economy for a number

02:12:36.550 --> 02:12:39.360
of years developed a fairly low

02:12:39.370 --> 02:12:41.580
level of average tariff, which

02:12:48.990 --> 02:12:52.520
covers the current and important

02:12:52.530 --> 02:12:55.540
problems related to Russia's

02:12:55.550 --> 02:12:57.520
entry into the WTO.